<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Suskin, Steven. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.playbill.com/features/article/66379-ON-THE-RECORD-Mamma-Elaines-King-Charlie-Brown/pg3">"ON THE RECORD: <i>Mamma</i>, Elaine's <i>King</i> &amp; <i>Charlie Brown</i>"</a> playbill.com, November 26, 2000.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Moscow1975-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Moscow1975_2-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1975">"9th Moscow International Film Festival (1975)"</a>. <i>MIFF</i><span class="printonly">. <a rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1975">http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1975</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved 2013-01-05</span>.</span></span></li>
</ol>
